This paper deals with adversarial attacks on neural network-based classifiers, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on developing new attacks against classifiers. The second most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the paper specifically mentions ImageNet and the Google Cloud Vision API. The third most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper deals with the security of machine learning systems. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with the limitations of current AI systems. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper proposes new methods for attacking classifiers under more restrictive threat models.
